Program: Free Thinking
Title: Breeding the Mongrel: Language Wars in Early Modern England
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03f8c5t
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 27 Aug 2014
Defenders of traditional English language and grammar often present themselves as purists but New Generation Thinker John Gallagher, from Cambridge University, argues that we have always borrowed words and adapted phrases. His essay outlines the impact C16th and C17th global exploration and trade had on our native tongue. Producer: Neil Trevithick First broadcast in October 2013. Show less